<TITLE> National booters to learn English from Daffodil University </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation on Tuesday signed a memorandum of understanding with Daffodil International University to improve the English language skills of the national footballers. "Daffodil University has shown their interest to improve the language skills of the national football team as well as the age-group teams and we have welcomed their initiatives from our heart," said BFF vice-president Badal Roy at a press conference after the MoU was signed. Roy also believed that this step would help the players greatly when they would come in touch with the foreign coaches and trainers during tours abroad. "Before teaching them, we will make categories on the basis of the players' educational background so that they can learn it easily," said Daffodil University register professor Dr. M Mizanur Rahman. Rahman also informed that they would start the class soon after the BFF provided them a list of players. BFF vice-president Kazi Badal Roy, general secretary Al Mussabir Sadi, technical director Shahidur Rahman Shantu, Daffodil University's dean of humanities and social science prof Dr. Shushil Kumar Das, assistant director M Mazbahur Rashid were present. bd
